        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Three giant centipede carcasses have wire springs that pull out and fling their sharpened legs around the room.</p>",
            "disable": "<p><span data-pf2-check=\"nature\" data-pf2-traits=\"mechanical, trap\" data-pf2-label=\"Bend Carapace DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"23\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Nature</span> (trained) to bend the centipede carapace so the wire can't pull out any more legs, or <span data-pf2-check=\"thievery\" data-pf2-traits=\"mechanical,trap\" data-pf2-label=\"Cut Wires DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Thievery</span> (expert) to cut the springy wires.<span data-visibility=\"gm\"> After all three carcasses are disabled (regardless of the check used), the trap is deactivated. The trap automatically deactivates after 10 rounds.</span></p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 5
            },
            "reset": "",
            "routine": "<p><span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> Each creature within 30 feet of a centipede carcass that hasn't been disabled takes [[/r 6d4 #piercing]]{6d4 piercing damage} (<span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-traits=\"mechanical,trap,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Avoid Carapace Strike DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"22\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save).</p>"
